Götarps brunn 16, tf. aman. v. Lunds hosp. 17, e. läk. v. Vänersb. hosp. 18, v. kustsanat. Apel-viken 19, und:läk. där 19-22, förste und:läk. 22-25, tf. und:läk. v. translated: Löfberg, Josef Henning, provincial physician, Tidaholm, b. 26/10/92 in Vallby, Kristianstad 1st, son of Anders L. and Boel Hemberg. Married in 19xx to Elsa Henrikson, daughter of director Sven H. and his wife Streiffert. Children: Kaj b. 20, Jan b. 25, Bo b. 32. — High school graduate in Kristianstad 11, Bachelor of Medicine in 14, and Doctor of Medicine in 19 from Lund University. Travelled to coastal hospital and Finsen Institute in Denmark in 23. Assistant physician at Götarps Spa from 16, temporary clerk at Lund Hospital from 17, assistant physician at Vänersborg Hospital from 18, coast sanatorium Apelviken from 19, junior physician there from 19-22, senior junior physician from 22-25, temporary junior physician at S:t Görans Hospital surgical tuberculosis department in 23, temporary physician at Styrsö coast sanatorium in 25, second junior physician at Hälsingborg County Hospital surgical department in 26, temporary provincial physician in the Kopparberg and Charlottenberg districts from 26-27, provincial physician in the Tidaholm district since 27, physician at Haga nursing home in Tidaholm. Naval medical scholarship from 16-19, naval medical officer of second group in reserve from 19, and of first group from 38. Chairman of the Red Cross Tidaholm branch from 28-43. Swedish Red Cross Medal of Merit recipient.
